  "raw_html": "<div class=\"section\" id=\"numel\">\n<span id=\"api-paddle-numel\"></span>\n<h1>numel<a class=\"headerlink\" href=\"#numel\" title=\"Permalink to this heading\"></a></h1>\n<dl class=\"py function\">\n<dt class=\"sig sig-object py\">\n<span class=\"sig-prename descclassname\"><span class=\"pre\">paddle.</span></span>\n<span class=\"sig-name descname\"><span class=\"pre\">numel</span></span>\n<span class=\"sig-paren\">(</span>\n<em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">x</span></span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">:</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">Tensor</span></span></em>, \n         <em class=\"sig-param\"><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">name</span></span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">:</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\"><span class=\"pre\">str</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\"><span class=\"pre\">|</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"pre\">None</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\"><span class=\"pre\">=</span></span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"default_value\"><span class=\"pre\">None</span></span></em>\n<span class=\"sig-paren\">)</span>\n<span class=\"sig-return\"><span class=\"sig-return-icon\">→</span> <span class=\"sig-return-typehint\"><span class=\"pre\">Tensor</span></span></span>\n<a class=\"reference external\" href=\"https://github.com/PaddlePaddle/Paddle/blob/release/3.3/python/paddle/tensor/stat.py#L352\"><span class=\"viewcode-link\"><span class=\"pre\">[source]</span></span></a>\n</dt>\n<dd>\n<p>Returns the number of elements for a tensor, which is a 0-D int64 Tensor with shape [].</p>\n<dl class=\"field-list simple\">\n<dt class=\"field-odd\">\n           Parameters\n          </dt>\n<dd class=\"field-odd\">\n<ul class=\"simple\">\n<li><p><strong>x</strong> (<em>Tensor</em>) – The input Tensor, it’s data type can be bool, float16, float32, float64, uint8, int8, int32, int64, complex64, complex128.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>name</strong> (<em>str</em><em>|</em><em>None</em><em>, </em><em>optional</em>) – Name for the operation (optional, default is None). For more information, please refer to <span class=\"xref std std-ref\">api_guide_Name</span>.</p></li>\n</ul>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"field-even\">\n           Returns\n          </dt>\n<dd class=\"field-even\">\n<p>The number of elements for the input Tensor, whose shape is [].</p>\n</dd>\n<dt class=\"field-odd\">\n           Return type\n          </dt>\n<dd class=\"field-odd\">\n<p>Tensor</p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<p class=\"rubric\">Examples</p>\n<div class=\"highlight-python notranslate\">\n<div class=\"highlight\">\n<pre><span></span><span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">paddle</span>\n\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">paddle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">full</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">shape</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">4</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">5</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"p\">],</span> <span class=\"n\">fill_value</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">dtype</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"s1\">'int32'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"n\">numel</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">paddle</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">numel</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"gp\">&gt;&gt;&gt; </span><span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">numel</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">numpy</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"go\">140</span>\n</pre>\n</div>\n</div>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n</div>"
